name: Peter
about:
I am the Associate Director for Public Services at the Salt Lake County Library. I also a consultant offering keynote speeches, leadership training, interactive workshops, facilitations, and executive coaching.

As a Board Member with EveryLibrary (http://everylibrary.org), a nonprofit social welfare organization chartered to work on local library ballot initiatives, I provide tactical and operational support to local voter awareness campaigns. EveryLibrary works with local ballot committees and PAC leaders in support of local library ballot measures, and with library staff and leadership on effective Information Only campaigns. Additionally, we consult on specific state legislative measures which impact libraries' ability to act as districts, and operate independently to advocate for specific library initiatives among the voting public.

name: Daniel
about: Yes, I must confess. I often find myself more at home in these ancient volumes than I do in the hustle-bustle of the modern world. To me, paradoxically, the literature of the so-called "dead tongues" holds more currency than this morning's newspaper. In these books, in these volumes, there is the accumulated wisdom of mankind, which succors me when the day is hard and the night lonely and long.
